"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">kind of bad</a>.</p><p styl=
e=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But never mind that, the point is that:</p><ol style=
=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li s=
tyle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">People do not trust that congresspeople are no=
t insider trading, and are mad at Congress about it, but</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There is already a very clear law saying that cong=
resspeople are not allowed to insider trade.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 1=
6px 0;">So just writing a law saying =E2=80=9Ccongresspeople are even more =
not allowed to insider trade stocks=E2=80=9D does not seem helpful.[2] The =
obvious next move is to instead write a law saying =E2=80=9Ccongresspeople =
are not allowed=C2=A0<em>to trade stocks at all</em>, just in case they are=
 tempted to insider trade,=E2=80=9D=C2=A0and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/26356098.267642/aHR0cHM6Ly90aGVoaWxsLmNvbS9wb2xp=
Y3kvZmluYW5jZS81ODk1MDEtc2VuYXRlLWRlbW9jcmF0cy1pbnRyb2R1Y2UtYmlsbC10by1iYW4=
