ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
the bill text</a>. Basically owning stocks or bonds, or derivatives on stoc=
ks or bonds, would not be allowed except in a blind trust. Diversified=C2=
=A0mutual funds and exchange-traded funds are allowed, as are U.S. Treasuri=
es; =E2=80=9Cdiversified=E2=80=9D here means that a fund or ETF=C2=A0=E2=80=
=9Cdoes not have a stated policy=C2=A0of concentrating its investments in a=
ny industry,=C2=A0business, single country other than the United=C2=A0State=
s, or bonds of a single State.=E2=80=9D[3] So broad-market stock funds woul=
d be allowed but sector ETFs would not. (Exercises for the reader: Is the <=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/26356098.267642/aHR=
